===Etymology===
Latin ''miser.''

===Noun===
'''miser''' (''Plural:'' '''misers''')
# a person who [[hoard]]s [[money]] rather than [[spending]] it; a [[skinflint]] or [[scrooge]]. One who is cheap or  extremely [[parsimonious]].
#:''[[Ebenezer Scrooge]] was a stereotypical '''miser''', he spent nothing he could save; netiher giving to charity nor enjoying his wealth.''
